<TITLE> 2 bodies found floating near Indian border at Satkhira </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Satkhira, July 11 (bdnews24.com)Two bodies were recovered from Ichhamoti river in the Haraddoha area of Satkhira near the Indian border, police and family members said on Saturday. The dead were identified as Omar Ali, 35, son of Abdul Aziz from Garerkanda and Abdur Rahman, 20, son of Akhter Ali frim Itagachha of Satkhira town. Omar Ali's brother Jamaat Ali Gazi told reporters that Omar and five other men went to India to buy cows about a week ago. "Since then they have been untraced," said Gazi. He said Omar's and Abdur's the floating bodies were rescued from the same area of the Ichhamoti river on the same day. Sub-inspector Ganga Rani of the Satkhira Sadar police station said the bodies were sent to the hospital morgue for autopsy. Deputy assistant director of 41 Rifles Battalion, Mahbubur Rashid, said he suspected that the two victims may have been killed by India's Border Security Force. Last Thursday, BSF shot dead four Bangladeshi men, thought to be cattle traders, at the Agrobhulot border in Benapole, Jessore, raising cross-border tensions in the area, officials said. bdnews24
